This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL) because it focuses on the analysis of written text and the use of punctuation as a stylistic feature. It could also belong to the sub-category of digital libraries (cs.DL) because it deals with the analysis of literary documents. Additionally, it could be classified under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) because it uses quantitative analysis to distinguish between different authors and literary genres. Finally, it could be categorized under information retrieval (cs.IR) because it involves the extraction of information from textual data.
